parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To make or bring low, humble, humiliate; pass: To be humbled. From tapeinos; to depress; figuratively, to humiliate.
Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
Strong, powerful, mighty. From kratos; powerful.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Fitting season, season, opportunity, occasion, time. Of uncertain affinity; an occasion, i.e. Set or proper time.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I raise on high, lift up, (b) I exalt, set on high. From hupsos; to elevate.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
